<p>Well, i am new to recursion programming. I have understood recursion but i have a doubt that if we use loops within recursion and use a return on base condition than finally which one will return. I have a code which i have return to find a way if sum of numbers can add upto a specific number. Ex: If i have 1,4,45,6,10 and 8 as number than there is one way i can reach 22 without repeating any number.</p>  <pre><code>               import java.util.Scanner;                class TestClass {                public static int count=0; public static int test(int[] num, int t, int sum,int initial) {      int i=0;     if(sum==0)     {         System.out.println("True");         System.exit(0);      }     else if(sum&lt;0)     {     return 0;     }     else     {         for( i=initial;i&lt;t;i++)         {      test(num,t,(sum-num[i]),i+1);           }     }       return 0;// i used it since it was necessary to return a value outside if-else }   public static void main(String args[] ) throws Exception {    Scanner in=new Scanner(System.in);    int t,i;    t=in.nextInt();    int[] num=new int[t];    for(i=0;i&lt;t;i++)    num[i]=in.nextInt();    int sum=in.nextInt();          int check=test(num,t,sum,0);    if(check==0)    System.out.println("False");     } </code></pre>  <p>}</p>  <p>Now in this program i just want to print either true or false. just one true or one false.</p>